				<h2 class="heading">Our Story </h2>
				<p class="details">Our founding team met in late 2013 at a hackathon held at Boston Children’s Hospital (<a href="http://www.hackingpediatrics.com/">www.hackingpediatrics.com</a>). The team that we led won the hackathon, and a few of us stepped away to rethink what the most meaningful business would be to have an impact on gaps in nutrition and how we choose to eat as a society. After months of research into healthcare challenges and food sourcing challenges, the issues became clear, we formed the company and started to build the technology, the team and the plan to evolve. </p>

				<p class="details">Today our team is inspired to offer the best possible guidance to people who have to change the way that they eat because of a medical condition, a dietary restriction or normal changes in the family. We work everyday with a love for good food, a love for what we’re doing, a passion to support those who need our help and a respect for anyone who takes on any medical and practical challenges at their table, and still demands great taste and variety in their meals.</p> 

				<div class="col-xs-12 team-images-container">
					<div class="col-xs-4">
						<%=image_tag("people/tara-history.jpg", class: "img-responsive")%>
					</div>
					<div class="col-xs-4">
