					</div>
				</div>
				<h2 class="heading">The problem we see and our vision</h2>

				<p class="details">Everyone in our society has a complicated and intimate relationship with the food that we eat, both as individuals and as families. Over the past century we have detached from our food sources and put our trust in manufacturers and stores to find and filter what we eat. Unfortunately, we have lost a lot in that process, including taste, variety and the ability to feed ourselves with confidence. We have lost the base of knowledge and skills that allow us to make wise choices and prepare delicious food with relative ease. </p>

				<p class="details">Now, with an increase in dietary restrictions as well as the prospect of the use of nutrition as part of our medical care, our society has a challenge to enable the practical use of nutrition guided prevention and treatment. Instead of offering practical support, we leave patients to learn everything on their own, mostly leveraging information that exists online, fragmented, riddled with misinformation and alarmist rhetoric, unfiltered for quality and not personalized. Patients have to learn and change their day-to-day, most often starting from a point where limited food selection and cooking is foreign. </p>

				<p class="details">At Kindrdfood, we believe that everyone should be able to enjoy great tasting food that is healthy and safe. A family taking on change should not feel limited or have to eat food that isn’t healthy, fulfilling and tasty. The path of change starts with excellent guidance, which begins with an expert. Our team of Registered Dietitian Nutritionists and seasoned chefs, come together to assure that our members are matched with the best fit for 1-on-1 personalized guidance, and that all supplemental education materials, recipes and meal plans are verified healthy, safe, and great tasting. </p>

				<p class="details">Kindrdfood’s solution was founded on the vision that support, tools and information should all be in one place, should be accessible when and where you need it, should be of the highest quality and come from verified sources, should be personalized to everyone at the table, should be coordinated with healthcare, but most importantly should be focused on great taste and enjoying every bite. </p>
			</div>
